sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64041
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP secretion circuit with the sigE chaperone and sopB secretion signal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly compatibility in mind, it might contain scar sequence cutsites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of the 168 amino acid secretion signal of sopB in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System (T3S). When fused to a protein of interest this signal, when co-expressed with the cognate chaperone sigE (BBa_J64025), will be directed to the T3S secretion apparatus for export to the extracellular environment. The co-expression of the chaperone is critical for high titers of secreted protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compatibility to biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the natural RBS for the sopB gene in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with consideration for biobrick standard assembly in mind. This RBS hasn't been explicitly tested for expression rate in a Fluorescence or B-Gal assay.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a cognate secretion chaperone for the sopB secretion signal in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the natural RBS for the sigE chaperone (BBa_J64025) in Salmonella Typhimurium LT2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compatibility to biobrick standard assembly in mind. This RBS has not been explicitly assayed for expression rate.
